# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# OSCAR — Onshape-Synced Copilot for Automated Reviews
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials.
# NEVER commit .env to source control.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── GitHub Copilot (PRIMARY — free for students) ──────────────────────────────
#
# OSCAR uses GitHub Copilot as its default AI backend, which is FREE for
# students through the GitHub Student Developer Pack.
#
# Steps to get your token:
#   1. Verify student status at https://education.github.com/students
#   2. Activate GitHub Copilot Individual (free for students) at
#      https://github.com/settings/copilot
#   3. Create a Personal Access Token (classic) at
#      https://github.com/settings/tokens/new
#      — Token name: OSCAR
#      — Expiration: 90 days (or no expiration)
#      — Scopes: check "GitHub Copilot" (listed under the "Copilot" section)
#   4. Paste the generated token below.
#
# The token is exchanged server-side for a short-lived Copilot session token
# via the GitHub Copilot internal API — your PAT is NEVER sent to the browser.
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_github_personal_access_token

# ── Onshape credentials (choose one method) ──────────────────────────────────

# Method 1: API Keys (recommended for personal/internal use)
# Generate at https://dev-portal.onshape.com → API Keys
ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY=your_onshape_access_key
ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY=your_onshape_secret_key

# Method 2: OAuth access token (use if you have an Onshape OAuth app)
# ONSHAPE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_oauth_token

# ── Additional AI providers (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Only needed if you want to use these providers in addition to Copilot.

# OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key

# Anthropic
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_key

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PORT=3000

# Comma-separated list of allowed CORS origins (explicit http/https only; no wildcard).
# When not set, all cross-origin requests are blocked.
# Example for local dev + production:
# ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,https://your-onshape-app.example.com

